===Etymology===
From earlier {{m|en|twise}}, from {{inh|en|enm|twies}}, {{m|enm|twiȝes}}, from {{inh|en|ang|twīġes||twice}}, from {{m|ang|twīwa}}, {{m|ang|twīġa}} {{gloss|"twice"; whence Middle English {{m|enm|twie||twice}}}} + {{m|ang|-es|pos=adverbial genitive ending}}. Related to {{cog|stq|twäie||twice}}, {{cog|gml|twiges}}, {{m|gml|twies||twice}}, {{cog|gmh|zwies||twies}}. Compare also [[twi-]] meaning two or both.

